s you make now may not work as financial conditions change.  Monitor your results to ensure cash budget requirements are being met and to evaluate if changing market conditions should alter your future decisions regarding amounts and length of time for investments.<strong>  </strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Institutionalize the process – </strong>Once you develop a structured and formalized system for investing your public funds, execute this process year after year to improve your investment performance and add additional dollars to your budget.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Next month, we’ll cover investment alternatives available under Michigan Compiled Law (MCL).</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>If you have questions regarding the new banking regulations or determining effective investment processes and options, please contact us at </em><a href="mailto:footnotes@umbaugh.com"><em>footnotes@umbaugh.com</em></a><em>.</em></p>', 'The Impact of Banking Regulations, Part 1', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '77-revision-2', '', '', '2012-01-09 15:58:50', '2012-01-09 15:58:50', '', 77, 'http://cashadvisory.umbaugh.com/77-revision-2', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
